43:54.340 --> 43:56.216
(music ends)

44:00.387 --> 44:02.139
(audience member coughs)

44:03.724 --> 44:06.060
(somber music playing)

44:13.233 --> 44:15.569
I, uh--
(clears throat)

44:16.320 --> 44:18.572
I watched you die...

44:18.655 --> 44:22.451
and all I could think about
was how none of it felt real.

44:26.455 --> 44:28.999
The lights,
the heavy boots
of the EMTs

44:29.083 --> 44:32.169
and their respectful,
quiet voices...

44:34.088 --> 44:36.048
"Let's lift him on three."

44:39.009 --> 44:40.719
It was so quiet.

44:43.847 --> 44:44.973
(Rue exhales)

44:46.016 --> 44:47.226
I was numb.

44:47.851 --> 44:49.770
I didn't care.

44:49.853 --> 44:53.816
I wasn't feeling life
in the way it was meant
to be felt because...

44:55.442 --> 44:58.570
I wasn't present.
I wasn't actually there.

44:58.654 --> 45:00.489
I was just watching it.

45:06.078 --> 45:07.996
But that's not true.
(sniffles)

45:10.332 --> 45:12.793
(crying) I do care.

45:16.422 --> 45:17.840
And what if...

45:20.884 --> 45:23.804
what if... the reason
it felt like a movie

45:23.887 --> 45:27.266
was because I wanted
to believe that losing you...

45:28.350 --> 45:30.686
is a part of a larger story.

45:32.896 --> 45:34.690
One that maybe I could...

45:35.858 --> 45:37.776
maybe I could still shape.

45:40.404 --> 45:41.905
(Rue sobbing)

45:45.284 --> 45:50.789
I... I remember
a couple of days before
you passed away.

45:52.374 --> 45:53.709
You told me...

45:55.002 --> 45:57.337
that if I ever wanted
to be with you...

45:59.339 --> 46:01.842
all I would have to do
is close my eyes...

46:03.260 --> 46:05.304
and we'd be together.

46:06.388 --> 46:07.514
(crying)

46:12.352 --> 46:13.645
You said that...

46:14.855 --> 46:17.649
memories exist
outside of time...

46:18.859 --> 46:21.320
and have no
beginning or end.

46:23.739 --> 46:26.825
You said as long as I live...

46:26.909 --> 46:29.036
you'll be with me forever.

46:32.331 --> 46:33.373
(sniffles)

46:34.249 --> 46:36.001
I miss you, Dad.

46:38.962 --> 46:41.131
I miss you until
I close my eyes.

46:43.467 --> 46:44.760
That's it.

46:44.843 --> 46:46.595
(paper rustling)

46:46.678 --> 46:48.222
Thank you.

46:51.683 --> 46:53.769
♪ ♪

47:10.285 --> 47:12.788
(line ringing)

47:14.164 --> 47:15.415
Lexi (on phone):
Hey.

47:16.083 --> 47:17.459
Hey.

47:18.293 --> 47:19.461
Um...

47:21.421 --> 47:24.383
I, I just, I just wanted
to tell you that I...

47:25.759 --> 47:28.387
I thought your play
was really beautiful.

47:31.223 --> 47:33.267
You might be the only
one who thinks that.

47:33.350 --> 47:36.228
(Rue chuckles):
Yeah, well, could you
imagine if I, like,

47:36.311 --> 47:38.438
hated it and Cassie loved it?

47:38.522 --> 47:40.232
(both laughing)

47:42.192 --> 47:44.194
Um, but what are
you doing today?

47:44.278 --> 47:45.779
Um, I was--

47:48.031 --> 47:50.242
Yeah, just laying in bed.

47:50.325 --> 47:52.244
(laughs)

47:52.327 --> 47:56.373
Cool, well, um, can I...
maybe, like, come over?

47:57.875 --> 47:58.917
Yeah.

47:59.710 --> 48:00.794
Totally.

48:00.877 --> 48:03.589
Okay cool.
I'll... see you later then.

48:03.672 --> 48:05.424
-Okay.
-Okay, bye.

48:13.807 --> 48:16.310
(melancholy music playing)

48:16.393 --> 48:18.520
(indistinct chatter)

48:38.165 --> 48:40.083
♪ ♪

48:57.225 --> 49:00.520
I feel like all
the kids in high school
are super crazy.

49:00.604 --> 49:02.314
It's literally
the same as eighth grade.

49:02.397 --> 49:04.983
People are just
way more dramatic.

49:05.067 --> 49:07.486
All the senior guys
are, like, nice.

49:08.320 --> 49:10.072
How are you
feeling?

49:11.907 --> 49:14.076
I don't know.
I'm okay.

49:14.159 --> 49:16.119
♪ ♪

49:24.711 --> 49:26.046
All right, all right.
I never see the five

49:26.129 --> 49:27.130
of you little
babies together,

49:27.214 --> 49:28.715
so we're gonna take
a photo, okay?

49:28.799 --> 49:30.550
-No, Mom, please
don't take a photo.
-All right, everyone come

49:30.634 --> 49:32.052
together like that.
Beautiful!

49:32.135 --> 49:33.929
-Mom, no one wants
to remember this moment.
-Oh, you little

49:34.012 --> 49:36.431
-sugar sweethearts.
-Please, stop, stop.

49:37.265 --> 49:39.393
(audience applauds)

49:46.108 --> 49:47.693
Rue:
I think your play
was the first time

49:47.776 --> 49:50.612
I was able to look at my life
and not hate myself...

49:52.447 --> 49:54.199
for everything I've done.

49:55.951 --> 49:57.285
What do you mean?

50:00.497 --> 50:03.667
I don't know.
I think I've been
through a lot.

50:05.293 --> 50:07.254
And I don't know
what to do with it.

50:09.506 --> 50:11.842
But you've been through a lot
and you know what to do with it.

50:11.925 --> 50:15.846
-I don't know about that.
-Lex, look what you made.

50:17.139 --> 50:19.725
I don't know how to do that.

50:25.814 --> 50:28.692
I don't know how to get
to where you are.

50:33.989 --> 50:37.325
But I just wanted you
to know that seeing it
meant the world to me.

50:41.246 --> 50:42.456
(soft chuckle)

50:55.051 --> 50:57.471
Do you think about
your dad often?

51:03.435 --> 51:04.436
Me too.

51:04.519 --> 51:06.146
Rue:
I feel like I had
so much to learn

51:06.229 --> 51:09.274
from him still,
you know?

51:09.357 --> 51:11.568
I also think I'm
really angry about it.

51:12.194 --> 51:13.779
Lexi: Yeah.

51:16.823 --> 51:20.035
Rue:
Do you ever...
get angry about it?

51:21.828 --> 51:24.748
It's a bit more
complicated than that.

51:24.831 --> 51:26.541
Rue:
What do you mean?

51:26.625 --> 51:28.418
I think, like...

51:28.502 --> 51:31.505
I was kind of relieved
when he stopped showing up.

51:31.588 --> 51:34.341
'Cause I was so worried
something bad was gonna happen.

51:39.721 --> 51:40.847
I get that.

51:42.766 --> 51:43.809
Lexi: Now...

51:43.892 --> 51:47.062
every time the phone rings,
it's like...

51:48.980 --> 51:50.106
You know?

52:01.034 --> 52:03.161
But you figured it out.

52:05.038 --> 52:06.790
You fuckin' figured it out.

52:12.003 --> 52:14.422
When my dad died,
everybody would
tell me that...

52:14.506 --> 52:16.341
he died
for a reason.

52:18.176 --> 52:21.721
Ah, that shit
used to piss me off.

52:21.805 --> 52:24.224
I would literally wanna
fucking strangle them.

52:27.686 --> 52:29.563
But...

52:29.646 --> 52:33.316
I think what they're
actually saying is that
you gotta give it a reason.

52:38.029 --> 52:40.240
You gotta give all
this shit a reason.

52:44.035 --> 52:47.414
Because I don't wanna
hold on to this forever.

52:50.333 --> 52:53.420
I can't, I can't
hold on to it forever.

52:57.549 --> 52:59.217
Just doesn't feel good.

53:01.344 --> 53:02.721
It's just--

53:02.804 --> 53:06.099
-I know other people are,
like, built different, but--
-Yeah.

53:08.935 --> 53:10.562
it's too much for me.

53:14.316 --> 53:17.027
-I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
-No.

53:17.110 --> 53:20.322
-No, sorry.
-I'm sorry. I didn't--

53:24.117 --> 53:25.368
Lexi...

53:26.870 --> 53:29.414
I promise you,
it's not all his fault.

53:35.670 --> 53:37.422
I don't know for certain...

53:41.051 --> 53:42.260
but I'm, uh...

53:44.763 --> 53:46.389
I'm pretty sure he
wakes up every day

53:46.473 --> 53:48.934
and he thinks,
"I'm gonna be better for her.

53:50.393 --> 53:52.354
I'm gonna be there for her."

53:59.110 --> 54:00.862
That's also the problem.

54:02.530 --> 54:04.783
Because he only wants
to be better for you.

54:09.162 --> 54:10.789
(inhales, exhales)

54:13.333 --> 54:16.878
Because I know that
he loves you a lot more
than he loves himself.

54:21.341 --> 54:22.842
Mm.

54:22.926 --> 54:25.637
Rue:
I don't know if that
made you feel better.

54:28.598 --> 54:29.849
Thank you.

54:41.403 --> 54:43.154
(Lexi crying)

54:44.781 --> 54:46.199
(softly): It's okay.

55:06.136 --> 55:07.804
I miss you.

55:10.765 --> 55:12.684
(curtain pulling)

55:16.855 --> 55:18.982
(applause, cheering)

55:27.157 --> 55:29.367
(cheering continues)

55:49.345 --> 55:51.890
-(cheering)
-(whistling)

55:54.184 --> 55:56.144
(cheering continues, muffled)

56:26.132 --> 56:28.051
Cassie:
Do you know what's funny?

56:30.637 --> 56:33.932
Nate broke up with me before
I even went on that stage.

56:37.727 --> 56:39.020
Don't worry.

56:40.146 --> 56:42.232
This is just the beginning.

57:10.260 --> 57:12.387
(indistinct chatter)

57:45.336 --> 57:46.880
Jules: Sorry.

57:46.963 --> 57:48.214
Sorry.

57:48.882 --> 57:50.258
Sorry.

57:50.884 --> 57:52.093
Hi!

57:56.306 --> 57:57.432
(sniffles)

58:00.852 --> 58:04.814
I know you're probably
still really angry at me...

58:06.274 --> 58:10.987
but I just wanted to tell
you that I love you.

58:13.698 --> 58:15.450
And I miss you.

58:16.326 --> 58:17.744
So much.

58:38.765 --> 58:40.266
(kisses)

58:52.987 --> 58:54.447
(door shuts)

58:59.452 --> 59:01.871
(melancholy music playing)

59:08.294 --> 59:11.172
Rue:
Jules was my first love.

59:11.256 --> 59:14.008
I'd like to
remember it that way.

59:14.092 --> 59:17.011
I don't know if that's
actually true, though.

59:17.095 --> 59:19.305
I think I was high
for too much of it.

59:20.556 --> 59:22.267
I know it wasn't easy for her.

59:22.350 --> 59:24.269
And I hope she forgives me.

59:29.190 --> 59:32.568
I stayed clean through
the rest of the school year.

59:32.652 --> 59:35.989
I wish I could say that
was a decision I made.

59:36.072 --> 59:38.616
In some ways,
it was just easier.

59:40.660 --> 59:43.371
I don't know if this feeling
will last forever...

59:45.290 --> 59:47.000
but I am trying.

59:52.505 --> 59:54.465
I remember Ali said,

59:54.549 --> 59:57.468
"The thought of maybe
being a good person,

59:57.552 --> 1:00:00.430
is what keeps me trying
to be a good person."

1:00:02.849 --> 1:00:05.143
Maybe there's
something to that.

